listitem.para:
Example:
          [Address]
NFTSet=prefix:netdev:filter:eth_ipv4_prefix
          Corresponding NFT rules:
          table netdev filter {
        set eth_ipv4_prefix {
                type ipv4_addr
                flags interval
        }
        chain eth_ingress {
                type filter hook ingress device "eth0" priority filter; policy drop;
                ip daddr != @eth_ipv4_prefix drop
                accept
        }
}

The Minimum Packet Unit (MPU) determines the minimal token usage (specified in bytes)
          for a packet. When suffixed with K, M, or G, the specified size is parsed as Kilobytes,
          Megabytes, or Gigabytes, respectively, to the base of 1024. Defaults to zero.
